<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<plist version="1.0">
  <dict>
    <!--
      Hardened-runtime entitlements for Restream Chat Plus Plus.
      Electron needs JIT + unsigned-executable-memory for V8.
      Required for notarization on macOS 10.14+.
    -->
    <key>com.apple.security.cs.allow-jit</key>
    <true/>
    <key>com.apple.security.cs.allow-unsigned-executable-memory</key>
    <true/>
    <key>com.apple.security.cs.allow-dyld-environment-variables</key>
    <true/>
    <!-- Outbound network for OAuth + Restream chat WebSocket -->
    <key>com.apple.security.network.client</key>
    <true/>
    <!-- Inbound localhost callback for OAuth redirect on port 8765 -->
    <key>com.apple.security.network.server</key>
    <true/>
    <!--
      v0.1.67 — `keychain-access-groups` REMOVED (Ethan voice 3995, 2026-05-24).
      v0.1.66 attempted to add `keychain-access-groups` to enable
      `app.configureWebAuthn({ touchID })` per Codex xhigh review feedback,
      but that entitlement requires a Developer ID provisioning profile
      (`Contents/embedded.provisionprofile`) on modern macOS — without
      one, `taskgated-helper` refuses to launch the app:

          taskgated-helper: Disallowing com.ethansk.restream-chat-plus-plus
          because no eligible provisioning profiles found

      The v0.1.66 signed build launched-failed with `launchd job spawn
      failed` (NSPOSIXErrorDomain 162) on macOS 25 — verified on the
      release Mini before this revert.

      Getting platform-authenticator (macOS passkey sheet) support back
      requires:
        1. Registering a keychain-access-group in App Store Connect for
           the Developer ID team (T34G959ZG8).
        2. Downloading the Developer ID Application provisioning profile
           that includes the group + bundle ID.
        3. Bundling that profile into `Contents/embedded.provisionprofile`
           at packaging time (electron-forge can stage this via
           `packagerConfig.osxSign.optionsForFile`).

      Until that's in place, RC++'s OAuth window can still complete
      Google sign-in via password / 2FA / security key — the passkey
      sheet just won't appear. The UA-strip + permission-handler fixes
      from v0.1.65 / v0.1.66 are still in place because they're useful
      regardless; only the platform-passkey-specific bits were reverted.
    -->
  </dict>
</plist>
